definitions.820-2850: What is 820-2850? a LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER.

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-2850</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> no video. surprise!?
threads.message:
i've got this <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-2850</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> with the non surprising no video issue. everything powers powers on and runs but no video on internal or external. i caught the video where pp1v8r was at 1.3v and louis injected 1.8v to make it work again. before i do that i noticed that on diode mode pad 1 of L9560 is .058. pad 2 is .133.

I'm thinking of changing <TRANSISTOR>Q9560</TRANSISTOR> to see if thats pulling it to ground, but want to check and see if anyone else had some ideas.
